National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan held a meeting with Akiba Takeo, Secretary General of Japan's National Security Secretariat. The discussion focused on the U.S.-Japan alliance and its role in maintaining peace and security in the Indo-Pacific region. They emphasized the need for timely investment in their joint strategic vision to promote a free and open Indo-Pacific. Both parties highlighted the importance of peace and stability in the Taiwan Strait and expressed their solidarity in opposing Russia's war on Ukraine. They also recognized the significance of bilateral and regional coordination in strengthening the rules-based economic order, including efforts to create more resilient supply chains and enhance energy security.